    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieved level 2 against a required level 3 due to single-rate testing; this gap is accepted given the quasi-static COU, ASTM F1717 protocol constraints, and corroborating literature evidence. All three QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percentage difference < 10%. The FEA ensemble is deemed credible for supporting the regulatory submission of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under ASTM F1717 compression-bending.",
